Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted @water{}.

Chop the @potatoes{2}(peeled) into 1cm chunks.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until fork tender, ~{10-15%minutes}—take care not to overcook!

When cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Peel half the @garlic{1}, pop into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose. Roast in the oven until softened, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Peel and grate the remaining @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Trim the root of the @baby gem{120%g}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

In a #salad bowl{}, mix the @apple cider vinegar{1%sachet}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and @oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then set aside.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the @Irish beef mince{250%g} until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Break it up with a spoon as it cooks.

When the mince is browned, add the grated garlic, @rogan josh curry paste{1%sachet} and @North Indian style spice mix{2%sachets}. Cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @beef stock{1%sachet} and @water{100%ml} into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Carefully add the cooked potato to the beef.

Stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Add a splash of @water{} if the mince becomes too dry.

> TIP: You don't want the mixture too wet or the naan will become soggy.

Meanwhile, pop the @naan{2} into the oven and bake until toasted and golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove the roasted garlic from the oven and mash with a fork.

Add the @yoghurt{75%g} to a #small bowl{} and stir in the roasted garlic. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then set aside.

Add the baby gem to the #bowl{} with the dressing and toss to coat.

Share the naans between plates.

Top each naan with the beef kheema and a handful of salad leaves.

Scatter over the chopped tomato.

Finish with a drizzle of garlic yoghurt.

Serve any remaining salad alongside.